item.title: Enhance your research with document uploads
item.description:
We’re thrilled to introduce a powerful new feature to Crunch: the ability to upload and integrate documents alongside your datasets!

Now, you can provide comprehensive support for your research findings by adding relevant documentation directly to your projects. Whether it’s a detailed PDF or PowerPoint report, a questionnaire with crucial data points, a Word document with your analysis, or even images, you can easily enrich your insights and enhance collaboration with your team.

item.title: New hypothesis testing features in Crunch
item.description:
Crunch tab book exports now include a new hypothesis testing option that computes all possible comparisons between columns of a two-way table. When users select the “Column t-test” option in the “Export tab book… > Customize” panel, columns in output will be lettered and differences that are significant at the .05 significance level are indicated by letters underneath the cell with the higher percentage. See here for details.
